The paper deals with identifying communities in multiplex networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social networks (cs.SOC) and network science (cs.SI). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational methods (cs.DS) to identify these communities. Additionally, the paper discusses the extension of a popular algorithm (clique percolation) to multiplex networks, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
